\cos(\pi/n)
  1 - \cos\frac{\pi}{n} = 2\sin^2\frac{\pi}{2n} <\frac{\pi}{2n^2}
\sum\limits_{n=1}^{\infty }{\left( 1-\cos \frac{\pi }{n} \right)}  =\sum _{n=1}^{\infty }{\frac { \left( -1 \right) ^{n+1}{\pi }^{2\,n} \zeta\left( 2\,n \right) }{ \left( 2\,n \right) !}} \sim 4.870718962.
